227
00:17:32,165 --> 00:17:33,546
Ah.

228
00:17:33,613 --> 00:17:37,507
Hell's waking up every goddamn day
and not even knowing why you're here.

229
00:17:38,917 --> 00:17:40,518
But I'm out now.

230
00:17:40,614 --> 00:17:43,961
It took somebody who was kind to me
getting killed to do it.

231
00:17:44,076 --> 00:17:47,931
But I'm out.
I know exactly what I gotta do.

232
00:17:52,199 --> 00:17:54,501
<i>So you were scared,
weren't you, Goldie?</i>

233
00:17:54,568 --> 00:17:57,119
<i>Somebody wanted you dead
and you knew it.</i>

234
00:17:57,196 --> 00:17:59,842
<i>So you hit the saloons. The bad places,</i>

235
00:17:59,910 --> 00:18:04,033
<i>looking for the biggest,
meanest lug around and finding me.</i>

236
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:06,661
<i>Well, I'm gonna find
that son of a bitch that killed you,</i>

237
00:18:06,728 --> 00:18:09,509
<i>and I'm gonna give him the hard goodbye.</i>

238
00:18:10,794 --> 00:18:13,662
<i>Walk down
the right back alley in Sin City...</i>

239
00:18:13,767 --> 00:18:16,769
<i>- Leave your hands off Nancy.
... and you could find anything.</i>

240
00:18:16,874 --> 00:18:19,454
That coat looks like Baghdad.

241
00:18:19,531 --> 00:18:22,945
So does your face.
Take off!

242
00:18:27,529 --> 00:18:30,464
He's new here, Marv.
He didn't know.

243
00:18:30,531 --> 00:18:32,871
<i>Kadie's is my kind of joint.</i>

244
00:18:34,635 --> 00:18:39,814
<i>Nancy's just getting started with her gig,
but already the crowd's breathing hard.</i>

245
00:18:39,881 --> 00:18:41,953
<i>Plenty of nights I've drooled over Nancy,</i>

246
00:18:42,020 --> 00:18:45,635
<i>shoulder to shoulder
with all the other losers like me.</i>

247
00:18:46,115 --> 00:18:49,021
<i>But that's not what I'm lookin' for tonight.</i>

248
00:18:50,056 --> 00:18:51,428
What'll it be, Marv?

249
00:18:51,495 --> 00:18:54,276
A shot and a brew, Shellie,
and keep 'em comin'.

250
00:18:54,343 --> 00:18:57,853
Sure, honey.
You take it slow, now.

251
00:19:11,941 --> 00:19:14,914
<i>Most people think Marv is crazy.</i>

252
00:19:14,981 --> 00:19:18,558
<i>He just had the rotten luck
of being born in the wrong century.</i>

253
00:19:18,664 --> 00:19:20,994
<i>He'd be right at home
on some ancient battlefield,</i>

254
00:19:21,061 --> 00:19:23,363
<i>swinging an ax into somebody's face.</i>

255
00:19:23,842 --> 00:19:28,158
<i>Or in a Roman arena
taking a sword to other gladiators like him.</i>

256
00:19:28,235 --> 00:19:31,975
<i>They'd have tossed him girls
like Nancy back then.</i>

257
00:19:34,631 --> 00:19:37,317
Show's over, dickwad.
Drink up.

258
00:19:37,384 --> 00:19:40,165
Now, that's one fine-looking coat
you're wearing there.

259
00:19:43,042 --> 00:19:47,549
Your killin' days are over,
you over-the-hill, do-gooder son of a bitch.

260
00:19:47,655 --> 00:19:52,412
<i>I love hit men. No matter what
you do to them, you don't feel bad.</i>

261
00:20:00,132 --> 00:20:02,433
- Take it off.
- What?

262
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:04,831
A fine coat like that,
and you're bleeding all over it.

263
00:20:04,898 --> 00:20:07,286
All right, it's all yours.
Oh, God!

264
00:20:07,363 --> 00:20:10,748
It wasn't you losers who killed Goldie.

265
00:20:10,825 --> 00:20:15,102
The guy who did that,
he knew what he was doing.

266
00:20:16,166 --> 00:20:18,305
So tell me, man.
Who sent you?

267
00:20:21,345 --> 00:20:23,455
I don't hear you giving me any names.

268
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:26,974
So I guess when I shot you in the belly
I aimed a little too high.

269
00:20:29,861 --> 00:20:34,436
You keep holding out on me like this,
and I'm gonna have to get really nasty.

270
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:42,750
It was Telly...
Telly Stern passed me the order.

271
00:20:43,652 --> 00:20:46,586
He runs the tables over
to the Triple Ace Club.

272
00:20:47,488 --> 00:20:49,885
Thanks again.

273
00:20:54,978 --> 00:20:56,800
<i>Then the damnedest thing happens.</i>

274
00:20:56,867 --> 00:21:00,828
<i>For a second, I smell the angel smell
that belonged to my Goldie.</i>

275
00:21:00,895 --> 00:21:03,292
<i>Just need my medicine, is all.</i>

276
00:21:03,781 --> 00:21:05,402
Bastard.

277
00:21:05,479 --> 00:21:08,442
You're gonna pay for what you did to me.

278
00:21:11,204 --> 00:21:12,825
Feel like talking, Louie?

279
00:21:12,902 --> 00:21:15,290
How many got paid off
for the frame, Louie? Huh?

280
00:21:15,366 --> 00:21:17,054
How many for the kill?

281
00:21:17,121 --> 00:21:19,615
It was Connelly.
He set me up.

282
00:21:22,079 --> 00:21:24,026
He'll never talk.

283
00:21:26,913 --> 00:21:29,982
I don't know about you,
but I'm havin' a ball.

284
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:34,978
<i>Connelly talks.
They all talk.</i>

285
00:21:35,841 --> 00:21:38,047
And what have been
your sins, my son?

286
00:21:38,114 --> 00:21:40,569
Well, Padre,
I don't want to keep you up all night,

287
00:21:40,646 --> 00:21:43,581
so I'll just fill you in on the latest batch.

288
00:21:43,648 --> 00:21:46,515
These here hands of mine,
they got blood all over 'em.

289
00:21:46,592 --> 00:21:48,635
You're speaking figuratively.

290
00:21:48,702 --> 00:21:53,113
When I need to find something out,
I just go out and look for somebody

291
00:21:53,190 --> 00:21:55,578
that knows more than me,
and I go and I ask them.

292
00:21:55,683 --> 00:21:58,714
Sometimes, I ask pretty hard.

293
00:21:58,819 --> 00:22:04,449
By way of a "for instance",
I killed three men tonight.

294
00:22:04,516 --> 00:22:05,820
Tortured 'em first.

295
00:22:05,887 --> 00:22:10,049
You might say I been
working my way up the food chain.

296
00:22:10,116 --> 00:22:12,802
First two were minnows -
small-time messengers.

297
00:22:12,869 --> 00:22:17,539
But it was Connelly, the money man,
who fingered you, Padre.

298
00:22:17,597 --> 00:22:20,215
Dear Lord, man,
this is a house of God.

299
00:22:20,292 --> 00:22:23,898
Just give me a damn name.

300
00:22:23,965 --> 00:22:27,168
- Roark.
- You really are pushing your luck, Padre,

301
00:22:27,235 --> 00:22:30,083
feeding me garbage like that.

302
00:22:30,141 --> 00:22:31,292
It can't be that big.

303
00:22:31,397 --> 00:22:33,593
There's a farm
at North Cross and Lennox.

304
00:22:33,660 --> 00:22:36,480
It's all there.
Find out for yourself.

305
00:22:36,547 --> 00:22:38,436
And while you're at it,

306
00:22:38,494 --> 00:22:43,644
ask yourself if that corpse of a slut
is worth dying for.

307
00:22:44,066 --> 00:22:46,041
<i>Worth dying for.</i>

308
00:22:46,108 --> 00:22:48,055
<i>Worth killing for.</i>

309
00:22:48,132 --> 00:22:50,395
<i>Worth going to hell for.</i>

310
00:22:50,462 --> 00:22:52,323
Amen.

311
00:22:55,679 --> 00:22:58,499
<i>His keys say the padre drove a Mercedes,</i>

312
00:22:58,556 --> 00:23:01,913
<i>or at least that's what they're
passing off as a Mercedes these days.</i>

313
00:23:02,018 --> 00:23:05,912
<i>Modern cars -
they all look like electric shavers.</i>

314
00:23:12,289 --> 00:23:13,853
Goldie.

315
00:23:16,452 --> 00:23:17,660
Goldie!

316
00:23:27,969 --> 00:23:30,070
It couldn't be Goldie.

317
00:23:30,146 --> 00:23:34,270
<i>It's my own fault, and nobody else's,
that I got confused.</i>

318
00:23:34,395 --> 00:23:37,981
<i>I've been having so much fun
I forgot to take my medicine.</i>

319
00:23:38,049 --> 00:23:39,899
<i>That wasn't Goldie back there.</i>

320
00:23:39,967 --> 00:23:41,338
<i>Goldie's dead,</i>

321
00:23:41,405 --> 00:23:45,203
<i>and that's the whole reason
that I've been doing what I've been doing.</i>

322
00:23:45,279 --> 00:23:48,924
<i>When you got a condition,
it's bad to forget your medicine.</i>

323
00:23:51,619 --> 00:23:56,884
<i>The cold thing, it creeps into my gut
and tells me one more time it won't let go.</i>

324
00:23:57,632 --> 00:24:00,115
<i>This is a bad place, this farm.</i>

325
00:24:00,192 --> 00:24:01,851
<i>People have died here...</i>

326
00:24:03,616 --> 00:24:05,179
<i>... the wrong way.</i>

327
00:24:07,807 --> 00:24:09,696
I don't want to fight, pooch.

328
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:15,287
I got no gripe with you.

329
00:24:17,598 --> 00:24:19,325
Easy, boy.

330
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:25,021
<i>No way I was gonna use
my gun on you, buddy.</i>

331
00:24:25,088 --> 00:24:27,706
<i>It's whoever owns you I'm curious about,</i>

332
00:24:27,773 --> 00:24:31,667
<i>because there's blood on your breath,
and I think I know what kind.</i>

333
00:24:32,156 --> 00:24:34,362
<i>So I sniff around to see what's buried.</i>

334
00:24:38,140 --> 00:24:39,550
Here we go.

335
00:24:44,633 --> 00:24:47,606
<i>It's impossible.
Nobody can sneak up on me.</i>

336
00:24:53,024 --> 00:24:57,628
<i>I go blind.
Not a sound. Nobody's that quiet.</i>

337
00:24:57,695 --> 00:25:01,176
<i>Nobody except the one who snuck
into that hotel room two nights ago.</i>

338
00:25:01,569 --> 00:25:05,041
It was you, you bastard.
You killed her.

339
00:25:05,501 --> 00:25:07,544
You killed Goldie.

340
00:25:07,649 --> 00:25:09,203
It was...

341
00:25:10,747 --> 00:25:12,214
<i>I blew it, Goldie.</i>

342
00:25:12,857 --> 00:25:15,254
<i>I found your killer,
but he was better than me.</i>

343
00:25:15,839 --> 00:25:17,815
<i>Too quiet, too quick.</i>

344
00:25:17,882 --> 00:25:20,270
<i>A killer born.</i>

345
00:25:20,347 --> 00:25:22,735
<i>Why didn't he finish the job?</i>

346
00:25:35,231 --> 00:25:38,808
He keeps the heads.
He eats the rest.

347
00:25:38,875 --> 00:25:42,107
- Lucille?
- It's not just that wolf of his.

348
00:25:43,804 --> 00:25:46,835
The wolf just gets scraps.

349
00:25:46,911 --> 00:25:48,791
Bones.

350
00:25:48,887 --> 00:25:51,131
It's him.

351
00:25:51,198 --> 00:25:55,447
He eats people.

352
00:25:56,319 --> 00:25:59,695
- He cooks them like they were steaks.
- Let's get you warm.

353
00:25:59,772 --> 00:26:01,939
Just like they were steaks.

354
00:26:02,016 --> 00:26:04,250
Now he's got both of us.

355
00:26:04,317 --> 00:26:07,415
It's all right.
Take a nice, slow breath.

356
00:26:08,154 --> 00:26:10,906
Just look at the heads on the wall.

357
00:26:11,002 --> 00:26:13,006
The heads on the wall.

358
00:26:13,658 --> 00:26:15,548
The heads on the wall.

359
00:26:15,643 --> 00:26:19,422
Son of a bitch!
He kept smiling that damned smile.

360
00:26:19,518 --> 00:26:23,479
He made me watch him
suck the meat off my fingers.

361
00:26:23,929 --> 00:26:26,164
- He made me watch!
- Oh, Jesus.

362
00:26:26,231 --> 00:26:30,968
He made me watch!

363
00:26:38,171 --> 00:26:40,444
Christ, I could use a cigarette.

364
00:26:41,144 --> 00:26:44,855
<i>Dames.
Sometimes all they gotta do is let it out.</i>

365
00:26:44,951 --> 00:26:48,116
<i>And a few buckets later,
there's no way you'd know.</i>

366
00:26:48,701 --> 00:26:50,705
You've brought us
some big trouble this time, Marv.

367
00:26:50,810 --> 00:26:55,184
Whoever's behind this whole thing has
his connections right in the department.

368
00:26:55,260 --> 00:26:57,399
Any leads?

369
00:26:57,466 --> 00:27:01,043
One guy I talked to told me
it was Roark running the show.

370
00:27:01,110 --> 00:27:05,752
Whoever it is, he knew I was checking out
that hooker almost before I did.

371
00:27:05,819 --> 00:27:09,300
- What hooker?
- The one you've been obsessing over.

372
00:27:09,367 --> 00:27:11,410
The dead one.

373
00:27:11,477 --> 00:27:13,587
Goldie.

374
00:27:13,654 --> 00:27:16,023
I didn't know she was a hooker.

375
00:27:16,119 --> 00:27:19,121
Doesn't make any difference
about anything.

376
00:27:21,048 --> 00:27:25,584
- But I didn't know that.
- She was high-class stuff.

377
00:27:25,661 --> 00:27:27,253
She must have shown you quite a time.

378
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:29,392
Quiet.
There's a car coming.

379
00:27:33,141 --> 00:27:35,510
Kevin!

380
00:27:36,469 --> 00:27:40,113
<i>All I've got is a face... and a name.</i>

381
00:27:40,181 --> 00:27:42,099
I'll see you later, Kevin.

382
00:27:51,641 --> 00:27:52,686
Let's go.

383
00:28:08,884 --> 00:28:10,648
They're done checking the house.

384
00:28:10,716 --> 00:28:12,653
They're coming this way.

385
00:28:12,730 --> 00:28:15,693
Bastards.
I'll show them.

386
00:28:20,603 --> 00:28:24,497
You're not gonna get
either of us killed, Marv.

387
00:28:24,602 --> 00:28:27,220
No, don't shoot!
Please.

388
00:28:27,287 --> 00:28:29,455
Listen to me.
I'm his parole officer.

389
00:28:29,531 --> 00:28:31,891
He's unconscious and unarmed,

390
00:28:31,958 --> 00:28:34,825
so there's no need to kill him.

391
00:28:40,819 --> 00:28:42,996
Captain, the target - there's no sign of him.

392
00:28:43,063 --> 00:28:44,243
Here's a sign!

393
00:28:58,427 --> 00:29:02,004
That there is one
damn fine coat you're wearing.

394
00:29:09,302 --> 00:29:12,783
<i>I keep coming back to that cop I just killed
and what he told me.</i>

395
00:29:12,850 --> 00:29:15,535
<i>I was pretty steamed about
what he'd done to Lucille,</i>

396
00:29:15,603 --> 00:29:18,058
<i>so I took my time
with that son of a bitch.</i>

397
00:29:18,614 --> 00:29:22,229
<i>It wasn't till I showed him
all those pieces of himself that he said it.</i>

398
00:29:22,776 --> 00:29:27,724
<i>Just a name -
Patrick Henry Roark, man of the cloth.</i>

399
00:29:27,830 --> 00:29:30,765
<i>Could've become president,
but he chose to serve God.</i>

400
00:29:30,870 --> 00:29:35,214
<i>Along the way, he happened to become
the most powerful man in the state.</i>

401
00:29:35,282 --> 00:29:39,060
<i>He's brought down mayors and governors
like they were nothing.</i>

402
00:29:39,127 --> 00:29:42,570
<i>He even made his rotten brother
a US senator without breaking a sweat.</i>

403
00:29:43,126 --> 00:29:47,432
<i>And here he's gonna get killed
in the name of a dead hooker.</i>

404
00:29:47,509 --> 00:29:52,208
<i>I'm getting used to the idea.
More and more, I'm liking the sound of it.</i>

405
00:29:53,685 --> 00:29:57,195
<i>Then it hits me like a kick in the nuts.</i>

406
00:29:57,300 --> 00:29:59,094
<i>What if I'm wrong?</i>

407
00:29:59,161 --> 00:30:00,945
<i>I've got a condition.</i>

408
00:30:01,012 --> 00:30:03,083
<i>I get confused sometimes.</i>

409
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:06,929
<i>And with Lucille dead,
I can't get my medicine.</i>

410
00:30:06,996 --> 00:30:09,106
<i>What if I've imagined all of this?</i>

411
00:30:09,173 --> 00:30:14,256
<i>What if I've finally turned into what
they've always said I was gonna turn into?</i>

412
00:30:14,323 --> 00:30:16,625
<i>A maniac.</i>

413
00:30:16,692 --> 00:30:18,993
<i>A psycho killer.</i>

414
00:30:19,061 --> 00:30:22,062
<i>Can't kill a man
without knowing for sure you ought to.</i>

415
00:30:22,129 --> 00:30:24,076
<i>I've gotta know for sure.</i>

416
00:30:27,030 --> 00:30:31,336
<i>The merchandise is on display
by the time I make my way to Old Town.</i>

417
00:30:31,441 --> 00:30:34,060
<i>For an hour or so,
I asked around about Goldie.</i>

418
00:30:34,136 --> 00:30:36,812
<i>I don't get any answers,
but I know I'm bound to.</i>

419
00:30:36,879 --> 00:30:38,922
<i>Lucille said Goldie was a hooker,</i>

420
00:30:38,998 --> 00:30:41,645
<i>and if she was, she has roots here -</i>

421
00:30:41,712 --> 00:30:44,436
<i>friends, maybe even family.</i>

422
00:30:48,943 --> 00:30:51,916
You can't be Goldie.
Goldie's dead.

423
00:31:01,430 --> 00:31:02,504
Ha.

424
00:31:02,609 --> 00:31:05,774
Goldie.
Yeah, sure, right.

425
00:31:05,841 --> 00:31:09,735
I haven't eaten anything
or taken my medicine for days now.

426
00:31:09,812 --> 00:31:12,267
No wonder I'm seeing things.

427
00:31:12,343 --> 00:31:13,744
Bastard!

428
00:31:19,248 --> 00:31:21,070
He's crazy.

429
00:31:21,138 --> 00:31:24,072
Hit him again, Wendy.
Harder.

430
00:31:25,655 --> 00:31:27,956
Wait a minute.
Why did she call you Wendy?

431
00:31:28,014 --> 00:31:30,258
Because that's my name, you ape.

432
00:31:30,833 --> 00:31:35,091
Goldie was my sister.
My twin sister.

433
00:31:35,158 --> 00:31:37,422
I guess she was the nice one.

434
00:31:43,348 --> 00:31:46,830
Goldie and the other six - where are they?

435
00:31:46,897 --> 00:31:48,805
What did you do to them?

436
00:31:48,882 --> 00:31:51,251
You crazy goddamn broad.

437
00:31:51,318 --> 00:31:53,226
Just take a look at this mug.

438
00:31:53,293 --> 00:31:57,321
Would any of you dames let me get
close enough to you to kill you?

439
00:31:57,398 --> 00:32:00,870
None of you would, but Goldie.

440
00:32:00,946 --> 00:32:03,977
And she only did because
she thought I could protect her.

441
00:32:04,082 --> 00:32:09,098
And I'll bet those cops didn't do a damn
thing about those other girls, did they?

442
00:32:09,165 --> 00:32:14,056
But as soon as they had me for a fall guy,
they showed up, guns blazing.

443
00:32:14,641 --> 00:32:19,340
But they didn't get me, and I've been killing
my way to the truth ever since.

444
00:32:19,407 --> 00:32:22,917
So, go ahead, doll.

445
00:32:22,994 --> 00:32:27,530
Shoot me now,
or get the hell out of my way.

446
00:32:34,032 --> 00:32:36,142
Aw, nuts.

447
00:32:36,622 --> 00:32:39,374
OK, I'm glad we got all that sorted out.

448
00:32:40,717 --> 00:32:45,291
- What the hell?
- I tied those knots! That's my specialty!

449
00:32:45,358 --> 00:32:47,152
You sat there and took it,

450
00:32:47,219 --> 00:32:50,067
when you could've taken my gun away
from me any time you wanted to.

451
00:32:50,125 --> 00:32:54,440
Well, sure, I thought I might be able
to talk some sense into you.

452
00:32:54,507 --> 00:32:57,643
And I probably would have had
to paste you one,

453
00:32:57,710 --> 00:32:59,715
and I don't hurt girls.

454
00:33:00,367 --> 00:33:02,026
I need a pair of handcuffs.

455
