It'll be the bad old days all over again.

909
01:02:46,580 --> 01:02:49,198
The pimps, the beatings,
the drugs, the rapes!

910
01:02:49,275 --> 01:02:53,072
They won't be watching the roads. Not yet,
they won't! Get me a damn hardtop!

911
01:02:53,139 --> 01:02:55,316
If I don't make it, you can have your war.

912
01:02:55,383 --> 01:02:57,867
Get that gun out of my face now!

913
01:03:00,409 --> 01:03:02,135
Bastard!

914
01:03:06,681 --> 01:03:08,819
I forgot how quick you are.

915
01:03:10,747 --> 01:03:12,339
<i>My warrior woman.</i>

916
01:03:12,406 --> 01:03:14,928
<i>She almost yanks my head clean off,</i>

917
01:03:14,995 --> 01:03:18,093
<i>shoving my mouth into hers
so hard it hurts.</i>

918
01:03:18,170 --> 01:03:21,459
<i>An explosion that blasts away
the dull, gray years</i>

919
01:03:21,526 --> 01:03:25,650
<i>between the now and that one fiery night
when she was mine.</i>

920
01:03:26,484 --> 01:03:29,170
A hardtop with a decent engine.

921
01:03:29,237 --> 01:03:31,510
And make sure it's got a big trunk.

922
01:03:33,495 --> 01:03:36,525
I'll always love you, baby.

923
01:03:36,631 --> 01:03:40,342
Always... and never.

924
01:03:48,024 --> 01:03:50,028
Where'd you find that heap?

925
01:03:50,105 --> 01:03:53,481
Just look at that trunk.
We'll never fit 'em all in.

926
01:03:53,557 --> 01:03:56,943
Gail? Unless there's something else
you want me to do,

927
01:03:57,010 --> 01:03:58,918
you think maybe I could go home?

928
01:03:58,995 --> 01:04:02,994
All this blood and stuff's got me kind of
feeling like maybe I'm gonna hurl.

929
01:04:03,061 --> 01:04:05,171
Sure, Becky, go home.

930
01:04:05,238 --> 01:04:07,923
But don't you talk to anybody,
not even your mom.

931
01:04:08,019 --> 01:04:10,800
They'll never fit in that trunk.

932
01:04:10,868 --> 01:04:14,483
Not like this, they won't.
Miho.

933
01:04:14,905 --> 01:04:16,785
Dry your hair as soon as you get home!

934
01:04:16,852 --> 01:04:18,895
You'll catch cold if you don't.

935
01:04:26,806 --> 01:04:28,331
Yeesh.

936
01:04:30,163 --> 01:04:32,656
Hey, Becky.
Gail said no calls.

937
01:04:32,723 --> 01:04:36,339
I just want to hear my mom's voice.
I won't tell her nothing.

938
01:04:36,406 --> 01:04:38,928
Please, don't say nothing to Gail.

939
01:04:41,364 --> 01:04:42,822
Hey, Mom?

940
01:04:46,552 --> 01:04:48,202
<i>Dizzy dames.</i>

941
01:04:48,279 --> 01:04:52,134
<i>What were they thinking, sticking me
with a beat-up bucket of bolts like this?</i>

942
01:04:52,211 --> 01:04:54,800
<i>We were barely able to get the trunk
to stay closed as it was,</i>

943
01:04:54,867 --> 01:04:56,459
<i>we packed it so tight.</i>

944
01:04:56,536 --> 01:05:01,235
<i>There wasn't anything we could do
but pile Jackie Boy in right next to me,</i>

945
01:05:01,302 --> 01:05:05,042
<i>out where anybody who cares to look
will see him.</i>

946
01:05:06,193 --> 01:05:09,972
<i>Go ahead, take one of his cigarettes.</i>

947
01:05:10,931 --> 01:05:12,686
<i>It'll help.</i>

948
01:05:36,182 --> 01:05:40,372
It's got you smoking there, bud.

949
01:05:44,755 --> 01:05:47,661
You shut the hell up, Jackie Boy.

950
01:05:47,766 --> 01:05:49,838
You're dead.

951
01:05:49,905 --> 01:05:53,962
I'm just imagining this, so shut the hell up.

952
01:05:54,038 --> 01:05:58,766
Well, it tells you something
about your state of mind, don't it?

953
01:05:58,833 --> 01:06:01,164
It's got you hearing things.

954
01:06:01,231 --> 01:06:04,271
It's got your nerves shot.

955
01:06:04,338 --> 01:06:06,822
It's got you smoking.

956
01:06:06,899 --> 01:06:10,677
You know it's true.

957
01:06:10,735 --> 01:06:14,254
Nobody ever really quits.

958
01:06:15,798 --> 01:06:20,363
A smoker's a smoker
when the chips are down.

959
01:06:20,430 --> 01:06:25,139
- And your chips are down.
- I'm fine. You shut the hell up.

960
01:06:26,453 --> 01:06:29,004
Will you look at that?

961
01:06:30,481 --> 01:06:33,799
Ooh, those hookers let you down.

962
01:06:35,094 --> 01:06:40,014
What are you gonna do
when you run outta gas, call AAA?

963
01:06:40,081 --> 01:06:44,137
You sucker for the babes, you.

964
01:06:44,204 --> 01:06:47,081
You ain't even gonna make it to the pits.

965
01:06:47,149 --> 01:06:50,150
You shut the hell up.
I'll make it.

966
01:06:50,256 --> 01:06:53,555
Not unless you keep
your eyes on the road, sugar pie.

967
01:06:54,063 --> 01:06:57,516
Watch it!

968
01:06:57,938 --> 01:06:59,875
Ah, this is great.

969
01:06:59,951 --> 01:07:03,183
Just like being in a buddy movie.

970
01:07:03,250 --> 01:07:05,514
Shut up!

971
01:07:09,839 --> 01:07:12,332
Boy, you're screwed.

972
01:07:12,399 --> 01:07:14,375
It's over.

973
01:07:14,452 --> 01:07:16,868
You're flushed.

974
01:07:16,945 --> 01:07:20,388
This time, I can't bring myself
to tell him to shut up.

975
01:07:20,494 --> 01:07:23,697
Sure, he's an asshole.

976
01:07:23,764 --> 01:07:26,276
Sure, he's dead.

977
01:07:26,353 --> 01:07:29,834
Sure, I'm just imagining that he's talking.

978
01:07:29,901 --> 01:07:33,795
None of that stops the bastard
from being absolutely right.

979
01:07:33,872 --> 01:07:37,190
I don't have a chance in hell
of outrunning this cop.

980
01:07:37,267 --> 01:07:39,405
Not in this heap.

981
01:07:39,472 --> 01:07:41,889
Pull over!

982
01:07:43,347 --> 01:07:46,723
The only question left
is whether I'm gonna kill him or not.

983
01:07:46,799 --> 01:07:49,168
Tough call.

984
01:07:49,235 --> 01:07:52,294
For all I know,
he's an honest cop, regular guy,

985
01:07:52,400 --> 01:07:56,428
a working stiff with a mortgage,
a wife and a pile of kids.

986
01:07:56,495 --> 01:07:58,701
My hand moves all on its own,

987
01:07:58,768 --> 01:08:02,633
sliding one of my guns to my lap
and thumbing back the hammer.

988
01:08:04,723 --> 01:08:09,384
- I don't know what to do.
- You better stop. You're making him mad.

989
01:08:10,698 --> 01:08:13,489
Whatever you say.

990
01:08:20,173 --> 01:08:23,683
Your friend here...
party a little too hard tonight?

991
01:08:25,227 --> 01:08:27,816
I'm the designated driver.

992
01:08:33,359 --> 01:08:36,428
Well, you're driving with a busted tail light.

993
01:08:41,482 --> 01:08:43,525
I'll let you off with a warning.

994
01:08:50,986 --> 01:08:52,415
What next?

995
01:08:56,491 --> 01:09:01,037
<i>The tank goes dry
a quarter mile from the pits.</i>

996
01:09:01,104 --> 01:09:03,952
<i>I shove the T-Bird the rest of the way.</i>

997
01:09:04,010 --> 01:09:07,146
<i>A few minutes' more work
and it'll all be over.</i>

998
01:09:07,213 --> 01:09:10,445
<i>Jackie Boy
will go into the damn tar pits,</i>

999
01:09:10,512 --> 01:09:14,568
<i>I'll catch a train out of Sacred Oaks,
go home and call it a...</i>

1000
01:09:25,520 --> 01:09:27,553
No more questions, Dallas.
Do what I say.

1001
01:09:27,659 --> 01:09:31,207
Clear the streets.
We're in lockdown.

1002
01:09:31,313 --> 01:09:33,864
We're not selling any tail in Old Town.

1003
01:09:33,931 --> 01:09:36,204
Not tonight.

1004
01:09:39,464 --> 01:09:42,917
Don't struggle.
You'll only hurt yourself.

1005
01:09:42,984 --> 01:09:45,161
Your cause is lost.

1006
01:09:45,228 --> 01:09:46,916
We know everything.

1007
01:09:46,993 --> 01:09:50,886
Soon the corpse of Detective Rafferty
will be in our possession,

1008
01:09:50,953 --> 01:09:55,748
and the truce between your prostitutes
and the police will be shattered.

1009
01:09:55,816 --> 01:09:58,856
There'll be arrests.
There'll be deaths.

1010
01:09:58,952 --> 01:10:02,663
My employer will seize
what remains of this neighborhood.

1011
01:10:02,759 --> 01:10:07,142
You will all be slaves.
Nothing can stop this.

1012
01:10:07,209 --> 01:10:12,004
But it is within your power
to save many lives

1013
01:10:12,071 --> 01:10:16,300
by facilitating the process of transition,

1014
01:10:16,367 --> 01:10:21,479
by negotiating the terms
of the surrender of Old Town.

1015
01:10:22,093 --> 01:10:24,481
Son of a bitch!
I know you.

1016
01:10:24,557 --> 01:10:29,477
I have suffered your kind before -
the dregs of Sin City.

1017
01:10:29,544 --> 01:10:31,491
I serve a new master now,

1018
01:10:31,596 --> 01:10:36,228
and soon you and all your wretched kind
will serve him as well.

1019
01:10:36,296 --> 01:10:41,513
Now, get dressed and shed a tear
for Dwight McCarthy if you must,

1020
01:10:41,580 --> 01:10:44,994
because, by now, he is surely dead.

1021
01:10:45,071 --> 01:10:47,717
You don't know him.

1022
01:10:47,785 --> 01:10:50,921
My man will find a way.

1023
01:10:50,988 --> 01:10:53,922
He always finds a way.

1024
01:10:55,342 --> 01:10:57,279
I can't fathom
these Americans always whining

1025
01:10:57,356 --> 01:11:00,587
and going on about how they got it so bad.

1026
01:11:00,655 --> 01:11:02,851
This is a fine, grand country.

1027
01:11:02,956 --> 01:11:05,219
Guiding light of the modern world, it is.

1028
01:11:05,287 --> 01:11:08,384
Low taxes, land of opportunity.

1029
01:11:08,461 --> 01:11:11,942
Where else would one bullet buy us
the fortune that we're getting for this?

1030
01:11:12,009 --> 01:11:14,531
Sure beats the living hell
out of blowing up airports and churches

1031
01:11:14,599 --> 01:11:16,871
without shite to show for it.

1032
01:11:18,694 --> 01:11:20,640
Yeesh.

1033
01:11:21,676 --> 01:11:23,201
You find something, Murphy?

1034
01:11:23,278 --> 01:11:26,433
Looks to be a poor, dead cop's badge.

1035
01:11:26,510 --> 01:11:28,418
It's all bent up.

1036
01:11:28,485 --> 01:11:31,238
What's this stuck in it?

1037
01:11:31,305 --> 01:11:33,280
Bloody hell.
It's the bullet.

1038
01:11:42,122 --> 01:11:45,632
You son of a bitch!
Bastard!

1039
01:11:46,985 --> 01:11:49,123
<i>They weren't cops, these four.</i>

1040
01:11:49,190 --> 01:11:51,099
<i>They were mercenaries.</i>

1041
01:11:51,175 --> 01:11:53,352
<i>And if they were hired
by who I think they were,</i>

1042
01:11:53,640 --> 01:11:56,229
<i>the bad times haven't even started yet.</i>

1043
01:11:56,297 --> 01:11:59,644
<i>And everything seemed
to be going so well.</i>

1044
01:12:11,085 --> 01:12:16,100
Remember, we don't have to
deliver every last inch of the man, Brian.

1045
01:12:16,167 --> 01:12:18,373
You got a good point there, Ronnie.

1046
01:12:18,440 --> 01:12:21,538
Lend me your knife.

1047
01:12:21,605 --> 01:12:24,578
Should I take a nap
while I'm doing all this waiting?

1048
01:12:24,645 --> 01:12:27,551
I'm at the bone, all right?

1049
01:12:29,670 --> 01:12:31,713
There we go.

1050
01:12:34,437 --> 01:12:38,532
Have you ever seen anything so pretty
in your whole life?

1051
01:12:39,462 --> 01:12:42,914
We'll be back for the three of you,
and if anyone happens by,

1052
01:12:43,020 --> 01:12:45,763
use your imagination, OK?

1053
01:12:55,171 --> 01:12:57,415
<i>Silence, now.</i>

1054
01:12:57,482 --> 01:12:59,783
<i>No air to breathe.</i>

1055
01:12:59,850 --> 01:13:03,744
<i>Only the horrid, oily tar taste
creeping up my nostrils.</i>

1056
01:13:04,962 --> 01:13:09,124
<i>Let it in.
Let it fill your lungs.</i>

1057
01:13:09,191 --> 01:13:12,701
<i>They were counting on you
and you blew it.</i>

1058
01:13:13,641 --> 01:13:17,794
<i>Skinny, steely fingers at my wrist.</i>

1059
01:13:17,861 --> 01:13:21,409
<i>Miho, you're an angel.</i>

1060
01:13:21,476 --> 01:13:23,298
<i>You're a saint.</i>

1061
01:13:23,366 --> 01:13:25,504
<i>You're Mother Teresa.</i>

1062
01:13:25,571 --> 01:13:27,547
<i>You're Elvis.</i>

1063
01:13:27,624 --> 01:13:29,762
<i>You're God.</i>

1064
01:13:30,433 --> 01:13:35,804
<i>And if you'd shown up ten minutes
earlier, we'd still have Jackie Boy's head.</i>

1065
01:13:36,226 --> 01:13:39,103
Dwight, they got Gail!

1066
01:13:40,100 --> 01:13:43,198
It's a cinch.
You got yourselves a spy in Old Town.

1067
01:13:43,303 --> 01:13:46,046
A stoolie who sold you out to the mob.

1068
01:13:46,113 --> 01:13:48,453
We gotta find out who it is and rescue Gail.

1069
01:13:48,520 --> 01:13:50,429
But first, we gotta get
our hands on Jackie Boy's head

1070
01:13:50,534 --> 01:13:54,524
before it gets to wherever it's going
and this whole situation blows wide open.

1071
01:13:54,601 --> 01:13:59,616
Miho, I hope to hell
you left one of 'em alive enough to talk.

1072
01:14:07,365 --> 01:14:10,328
<i>I let him know I'm not fooling around.</i>

1073
01:14:14,913 --> 01:14:16,888
<i>We talk.</i>

1074
01:14:25,577 --> 01:14:29,221
<i>Stay smart.
Stay cool.</i>

1075
01:14:29,288 --> 01:14:32,597
<i>It's time to prove to your friends
that you're worth a damn.</i>

1076
01:14:32,674 --> 01:14:35,714
<i>Sometimes, that means dying.</i>

1077
01:14:35,781 --> 01:14:39,128
<i>Sometimes, it means killing
a whole lot of people.</i>

1078
01:14:39,204 --> 01:14:41,592
There they are.
What do we do?

1079
01:14:42,245 --> 01:14:43,741
We stop 'em, Dallas.

1080
01:14:51,652 --> 01:14:53,724
<i>Jackie Boy's head is so close to me</i>

1081
01:14:53,791 --> 01:14:57,474
<i>I could almost reach out
and grab it right then and there.</i>

1082
01:15:02,528 --> 01:15:04,637
Get the head!
Get the head!

1083
01:15:06,210 --> 01:15:08,186
I got it!
I got it!

1084
01:15:14,659 --> 01:15:17,469
Suck on this, you stupid slag!

1085
01:15:21,190 --> 01:15:23,933
<i>I can't tell if Miho is alive or dead,</i>

1086
01:15:24,000 --> 01:15:28,546
<i>but I'm on my feet and every ounce of me
wants to get some killing done.</i>

1087
01:15:31,202 --> 01:15:35,508
You want the head now, sweetheart?
So come down and get it!

1088
01:15:40,064 --> 01:15:42,173
Brave lad.

1089
01:15:42,240 --> 01:15:45,952
I could've put a bullet
straight down your ear just now,

1090
01:15:46,019 --> 01:15:49,634
if I hadn't got me revolver
all wet and useless.

1091
01:15:49,702 --> 01:15:51,898
You got the drop on me, love.

1092
01:15:52,003 --> 01:15:54,372
I'm as helpless as a baby.

1093
01:16:01,085 --> 01:16:03,809
I got to come clean with you, sweetheart.

1094
01:16:03,876 --> 01:16:08,700
It was an outright lie I was giving ya
about me revolver being wet.

1095
01:16:08,767 --> 01:16:11,289
You see, I'm not too fond of shootin'.

1096
01:16:11,366 --> 01:16:14,329
It's my preference to blow things up.

1097
01:16:14,406 --> 01:16:16,707
Once you blast the roof off a pub

1098
01:16:16,765 --> 01:16:20,380
and seen all the parts flying off people,

1099
01:16:20,448 --> 01:16:24,245
a little bang bang's
never gonna match the sight of that.

1100
01:16:24,322 --> 01:16:29,856
And here's me, with all these fine grenades
and such a sweet beauty of a remote.

1101
01:16:29,923 --> 01:16:33,241
But it's me knife I'll be doing you with.

1102
01:16:33,346 --> 01:16:35,869
You killed me mates.

1103
01:16:35,936 --> 01:16:40,213
Someone shoulda told ya - never give
an Irishman good cause for revenge.

1104
01:16:42,112 --> 01:16:44,183
<i>Deadly little Miho.</i>

1105
01:16:44,960 --> 01:16:47,645
<i>You won't feel a thing
unless she wants you to.</i>

1106
01:16:47,712 --> 01:16:50,398
<i>She twists the blade.</i>

1107
01:16:50,820 --> 01:16:52,162
<i>He feels it.</i>

1108
01:16:54,915 --> 01:16:58,492
<i>I tell Miho what we're gonna do
and how we're gonna do it.</i>

1109
01:16:58,588 --> 01:17:02,865
<i>I grab poor Dallas's car phone and make
the most important call of my life.</i>

1110
01:17:02,980 --> 01:17:07,737
<i>First, we gotta rescue Gail,
then comes the kill.</i>

1111
01:17:07,804 --> 01:17:11,601
<i>The big, fat kill.</i>

1112
01:17:21,508 --> 01:17:24,251
Do we just gotta stand here
and watch this?

1113
01:17:24,318 --> 01:17:26,361
What, are you kidding me, man?

1114
01:17:26,466 --> 01:17:29,756
I could watch old Manute do his thing
all night long and not get tired of it.

1115
01:17:29,823 --> 01:17:31,232
I mean, the man's an artist.

1116
01:17:31,328 --> 01:17:36,219
Only an artist should be allowed
to touch such a beautiful subject.

1117
01:17:36,286 --> 01:17:38,137
Your skin is perfect.

1118
01:17:38,205 --> 01:17:41,177
Your nerves, responsive.

1119
01:17:41,245 --> 01:17:42,491
Beautiful.

1120
01:17:42,558 --> 01:17:45,522
Just give them what they want, Gail.

1121
01:17:49,406 --> 01:17:52,340
- Becky?
- It's over, Gail.

1122
01:17:52,993 --> 01:17:56,637
There's no fighting them.
Dwight's dead.

1123
01:17:56,704 --> 01:17:58,804
They got what's left of that cop we killed.

1124
01:17:58,910 --> 01:18:01,758
The mob's gonna turn it over to the police
chief, the cops are gonna mow us down.

1125
01:18:01,854 --> 01:18:03,705
We gotta cut a deal.

1126
01:18:03,772 --> 01:18:07,224
You little bitch!
You sold us out!

1127
01:18:07,291 --> 01:18:10,197
I didn't have no choice!
They was gonna hurt my mom.

1128
01:18:10,274 --> 01:18:12,374
You gotta cut a deal with these people.

1129
01:18:12,441 --> 01:18:14,484
It's selfish, you holding out like this.

1130
01:18:14,561 --> 01:18:17,083
You're gonna get a lot of girls killed
for no good reason.

1131
01:18:17,150 --> 01:18:19,538
It wasn't your mom!

1132
01:18:19,615 --> 01:18:22,645
We could have protected her
and you know it.

1133
01:18:22,722 --> 01:18:25,302
It was the money, you stupid little bitch!

1134
01:18:25,378 --> 01:18:29,119
Sure, there's money. Sure, you could've
moved my mom into Old Town

1135
01:18:29,186 --> 01:18:31,833
and let her know
that her daughter's a goddamn whore.

1136
01:18:31,938 --> 01:18:33,942
Breaks your heart, doesn't it?

1137
01:18:34,048 --> 01:18:38,584
They offered me what you couldn't
never offer me - a way out.

1138
01:18:38,622 --> 01:18:40,473
I had to watch out for my own neck.

1139
01:18:40,540 --> 01:18:42,171
Your neck.

1140
01:18:42,238 --> 01:18:46,199
Your precious, scrawny, little neck!

1141
01:18:50,140 --> 01:18:54,034
