1354
01:32:34,020 --> 01:32:36,360
<i>How did they find out who you are?</i>

1355
01:32:36,456 --> 01:32:39,458
<i>And what have they done to you, baby?</i>

1356
01:32:43,016 --> 01:32:45,087
<i>Not a sound.</i>

1357
01:32:45,154 --> 01:32:47,772
<i>No sign of life.</i>

1358
01:32:47,849 --> 01:32:51,426
<i>Has Roark gone to all this trouble
just to torture a broken old man,</i>

1359
01:32:51,493 --> 01:32:55,109
<i>like a kid poking at a fly
when he's already torn his wings off?</i>

1360
01:32:55,176 --> 01:32:57,861
<i>What has he done to Nancy?</i>

1361
01:32:57,928 --> 01:33:00,547
<i>It's like all she ever does
is read and study and write.</i>

1362
01:33:00,930 --> 01:33:05,754
<i>No diary, no phone numbers
or addresses written down anywhere.</i>

1363
01:33:06,761 --> 01:33:10,559
<i>Closest thing to a clue
is a pack of matches from a lousy saloon.</i>

1364
01:33:11,268 --> 01:33:15,680
<i>It's a long shot,
but maybe she's got some friends there.</i>

1365
01:33:22,019 --> 01:33:24,129
<i>A dead end.</i>

1366
01:33:24,196 --> 01:33:27,744
<i>Nancy wouldn't have anything to do
with a pack of drunks and losers like this.</i>

1367
01:33:27,811 --> 01:33:31,590
<i>But if there's anything to be found here,
the faintest lead to wherever Nancy is</i>

1368
01:33:31,657 --> 01:33:34,592
<i>or whoever kidnapped her
and mutilated her, this is the place.</i>

1369
01:33:34,985 --> 01:33:39,483
Excuse me, miss. Wondering if you
could help me. I'm looking for somebody.

1370
01:33:39,588 --> 01:33:42,753
Cold night like this, everybody's
looking for somebody, stranger.

1371
01:33:42,849 --> 01:33:45,601
It's not like that.
Her name is Nancy.

1372
01:33:45,668 --> 01:33:48,037
Eyes to the stage, pilgrim.

1373
01:33:48,133 --> 01:33:51,230
She's just warming up.

1374
01:33:58,979 --> 01:34:01,799
<i>Skinny little Nancy Callahan.</i>

1375
01:34:01,856 --> 01:34:03,678
<i>She grew up.</i>

1376
01:34:03,746 --> 01:34:06,565
<i>She filled out.</i>

1377
01:34:06,632 --> 01:34:10,104
<i>Nancy Callahan, 19 years old.</i>

1378
01:34:11,974 --> 01:34:14,909
<i>And here I was,
expecting a skinny little bookworm,</i>

1379
01:34:15,014 --> 01:34:18,620
<i>maybe a bit too shy for her own good.</i>

1380
01:34:18,687 --> 01:34:24,355
<i>How little she told me about herself
in all her letters for all those years.</i>

1381
01:34:28,354 --> 01:34:30,627
<i>How the hell did they find her?</i>

1382
01:34:30,694 --> 01:34:33,111
<i>Then it hits me.</i>

1383
01:34:33,187 --> 01:34:35,355
<i>They were bluffing.</i>

1384
01:34:36,160 --> 01:34:38,941
<i>I've led them straight to her.</i>

1385
01:34:46,911 --> 01:34:49,788
<i>She hasn't spotted you yet.</i>

1386
01:34:49,893 --> 01:34:52,310
<i>Turn around and walk out the door.</i>

1387
01:34:53,413 --> 01:34:55,034
<i>Lead the creep outside.</i>

1388
01:34:55,110 --> 01:35:00,097
<i>Get that Beretta away from him somehow,
and kill him.</i>

1389
01:35:00,164 --> 01:35:03,962
<i>I'm just a horny ex-con
watching an exotic dancer.</i>

1390
01:35:04,039 --> 01:35:06,878
<i>Just a few seconds and she'll be safe.</i>

1391
01:35:07,587 --> 01:35:10,272
<i>No, Nancy.
Don't notice me.</i>

1392
01:35:10,340 --> 01:35:13,571
<i>Don't recognize me.</i>

1393
01:35:22,912 --> 01:35:24,821
There's no time to explain.

1394
01:35:24,926 --> 01:35:27,803
I've made a terrible mistake,
put you in terrible danger.

1395
01:35:27,870 --> 01:35:30,143
We need to get out of here
right this second.

1396
01:35:30,210 --> 01:35:33,922
Whatever you say, Hartigan.
Let me throw some clothes on.

1397
01:35:35,936 --> 01:35:40,577
And here I'd figured you'd forgotten
all about me. Me and my dumb letters.

1398
01:35:40,644 --> 01:35:42,946
Kept me going.

1399
01:35:44,126 --> 01:35:46,370
Kept me from killing myself.

1400
01:35:47,971 --> 01:35:49,947
Hurry up, will you?

1401
01:35:55,394 --> 01:35:58,108
Maybe I should drive.
Not a chance.

1402
01:35:58,885 --> 01:36:01,532
Nobody but me
can keep this heap running.

1403
01:36:07,104 --> 01:36:10,614
Besides, from the sound of things,
you might have to shoot somebody.

1404
01:36:10,690 --> 01:36:13,558
- I don't have a gun.
- Under the seat.

1405
01:36:15,140 --> 01:36:16,895
It's loaded and it works.

1406
01:36:18,813 --> 01:36:21,335
Yeah, this'll do.

1407
01:36:21,441 --> 01:36:24,759
Taken it to the range a couple of times.
Kicks like a mule.

1408
01:36:28,739 --> 01:36:33,783
Hartigan, there's so much
I've wanted to say to you.

1409
01:36:33,860 --> 01:36:36,315
You've never been far from my thoughts.

1410
01:36:36,382 --> 01:36:39,864
I've lain awake nights, thinking of you.

1411
01:36:39,940 --> 01:36:42,616
What are you talking about?

1412
01:36:42,683 --> 01:36:47,258
Keep driving, Nancy.
Keep driving and keep the car on the road!

1413
01:36:49,952 --> 01:36:51,803
<i>She's counting on you, old man.</i>

1414
01:36:51,870 --> 01:36:53,558
What are you doing?

1415
01:36:53,664 --> 01:36:55,965
<i>Prove you're still worth a damn.</i>

1416
01:37:01,691 --> 01:37:04,280
Try and keep it on the road, Nancy!

1417
01:37:06,946 --> 01:37:08,538
<i>He's a decent shot.</i>

1418
01:37:08,605 --> 01:37:11,386
<i>He's got skill,
but he's in too much of a hurry.</i>

1419
01:37:11,454 --> 01:37:14,321
<i>Throwing away bullets
like they were candy.</i>

1420
01:37:18,205 --> 01:37:20,181
<i>He doesn't know how to take his time.</i>

1421
01:37:20,257 --> 01:37:23,422
<i>Aim careful and look the devil in the eye.</i>

1422
01:37:31,612 --> 01:37:33,885
Stop the car, Nancy.
Gotta confirm the kill.

1423
01:37:33,952 --> 01:37:35,956
- What?
- Stop the car, now!

1424
01:37:36,033 --> 01:37:38,996
Right.
Stop the car, confirm the kill.

1425
01:37:45,374 --> 01:37:48,126
Sorry. I got a little rattled.

1426
01:37:48,193 --> 01:37:52,279
It's OK. You did great.
Sit tight. I'll be right back.

1427
01:37:52,346 --> 01:37:54,456
No!
Let me stay close.

1428
01:37:54,523 --> 01:37:56,949
Nothing can happen to me
when I'm with you.

1429
01:37:57,055 --> 01:38:00,085
Please?
Let me stay close.

1430
01:38:09,340 --> 01:38:12,955
<i>The stink - I almost gag.</i>

1431
01:38:13,022 --> 01:38:14,873
<i>His blood smells
even worse than he does.</i>

1432
01:38:14,940 --> 01:38:17,808
<i>- Jesus.
- And it's all over the place.</i>

1433
01:38:17,885 --> 01:38:22,191
<i>But the creep himself, he's gone.</i>

1434
01:38:22,267 --> 01:38:24,243
We're out of time.

1435
01:38:24,320 --> 01:38:28,597
<i>The sirens - I used to welcome the sound.</i>

1436
01:38:29,115 --> 01:38:31,867
<i>There's nothing to do now
but find a place to hole up for the night,</i>

1437
01:38:31,934 --> 01:38:35,540
<i>get Nancy calmed down and figure out
what on Earth I'm going to do next.</i>

1438
01:38:35,617 --> 01:38:39,031
<i>The stink - somehow it stays with us
all the way to the motel.</i>

1439
01:38:39,769 --> 01:38:41,716
Nancy, I went to your apartment.

1440
01:38:41,793 --> 01:38:45,562
Your window was thrown wide open.
The rooms looked almost empty.

1441
01:38:45,629 --> 01:38:47,796
That's why I was sure
you'd been kidnapped.

1442
01:38:47,873 --> 01:38:51,479
My window? Robbed again?
That's the third time this year!

1443
01:38:51,546 --> 01:38:55,027
I swore if I ever saw you again,
I'd show you I grew up strong.

1444
01:38:55,104 --> 01:38:58,585
But there I was, just like before,
scared and helpless.

1445
01:38:58,652 --> 01:39:01,107
- I'm such an asshole.
- You should sit down.

1446
01:39:02,297 --> 01:39:05,145
You'll feel a little bit better if you sit down.

1447
01:39:05,787 --> 01:39:07,993
<i>I've never been all that good with people.</i>

1448
01:39:08,060 --> 01:39:11,292
<i>When it comes to reassuring
a traumatized 19-year-old,</i>

1449
01:39:11,359 --> 01:39:15,099
<i>I'm as expert as a palsy victim
doing brain surgery with a pipe wrench.</i>

1450
01:39:15,166 --> 01:39:17,948
It's always been you, Hartigan.

1451
01:39:18,015 --> 01:39:19,894
All these years.

1452
01:39:20,959 --> 01:39:23,510
It's just nerves
making you say that, Nancy.

1453
01:39:23,577 --> 01:39:26,675
You're just exhausted.
You need to sleep.

1454
01:39:26,751 --> 01:39:29,811
- Sleep with me.
- Stop it, Nancy!

1455
01:39:30,233 --> 01:39:32,247
Eight years.

1456
01:39:32,342 --> 01:39:35,795
Why do you think
I kept writing you those letters?

1457
01:39:35,900 --> 01:39:37,972
It wasn't just gratitude.

1458
01:39:38,077 --> 01:39:41,041
I tried to fall in love with boys.

1459
01:39:41,117 --> 01:39:43,381
Even thought I did once or twice.

1460
01:39:43,448 --> 01:39:47,313
But I was already in love... with you.

1461
01:39:47,389 --> 01:39:49,969
That's enough.
Jesus Christ!

1462
01:39:50,046 --> 01:39:52,280
I'm old enough to be your grandfather!

1463
01:39:52,347 --> 01:39:54,937
- You're just scared.
- I'm not scared.

1464
01:39:55,608 --> 01:39:57,267
No.

1465
01:40:31,034 --> 01:40:34,103
There's wrong and there's wrong
and then there's this.

1466
01:40:34,170 --> 01:40:36,587
For God's sakes, you're just a kid!

1467
01:40:37,498 --> 01:40:39,473
I love you.

1468
01:40:43,933 --> 01:40:46,292
I love you, too.

1469
01:40:46,359 --> 01:40:48,181
With all my heart.

1470
01:40:49,399 --> 01:40:52,468
<i>Cold shower - it helps.</i>

1471
01:40:52,535 --> 01:40:53,782
No, Nancy.

1472
01:40:57,177 --> 01:40:59,344
Recognize my voice, Hartigan?

1473
01:40:59,421 --> 01:41:03,094
Recognize my voice,
you piece of shit cop?

1474
01:41:03,161 --> 01:41:06,834
I look different,
but I bet you can recognize my voice.

1475
01:41:06,901 --> 01:41:10,737
Sure.
I recognize your voice, Junior.

1476
01:41:13,691 --> 01:41:16,060
<i>Everything's gone straight to hell.</i>

1477
01:41:16,156 --> 01:41:18,486
<i>I've been suckered
into betraying the only friend I've got,</i>

1478
01:41:18,553 --> 01:41:22,102
<i>and put her in the hands of a murdering
rapist I thought I'd put down for good.</i>

1479
01:41:22,677 --> 01:41:26,197
<i>Suckered by a spoiled brat
son of a senator.</i>

1480
01:41:26,264 --> 01:41:28,172
<i>It's all gone to hell.</i>

1481
01:41:28,249 --> 01:41:30,138
Klump, it's me.

1482
01:41:30,196 --> 01:41:32,948
I got a dead man needs to be fetched.

1483
01:41:33,015 --> 01:41:34,962
I want you to set me up for a party.

1484
01:41:35,029 --> 01:41:37,369
I've already got the girl, you dumb shit!

1485
01:41:37,436 --> 01:41:40,179
Hey, it better be perfect
or I'm calling my dad!

1486
01:41:40,275 --> 01:41:42,673
My tools better be clean and sharp.

1487
01:41:42,778 --> 01:41:45,396
It better be ready!
It better be perfect!

1488
01:41:47,228 --> 01:41:52,522
I get to do whatever I want,
however I want, whenever I want it!

1489
01:41:53,049 --> 01:41:56,175
My dad - I'd love him if I didn't hate him.

1490
01:41:56,243 --> 01:41:58,899
He spent a fortune
hiring every expert on the planet

1491
01:41:58,966 --> 01:42:02,035
to grow back that equipment
you blew off from between my legs,

1492
01:42:02,102 --> 01:42:06,293
just so the old fart can hold out
some kind of hope of having a grandkid.

1493
01:42:06,360 --> 01:42:10,187
Although, as you can see,
there were some side effects.

1494
01:42:10,263 --> 01:42:12,364
I'm not complaining, though.
Since you've been gone,

1495
01:42:12,469 --> 01:42:14,128
I've been having the time of my life.

1496
01:42:14,234 --> 01:42:17,581
And now you've led me back
to your darling Cordelia.

1497
01:42:17,686 --> 01:42:19,691
We all wondered
who wrote all those letters.

1498
01:42:19,796 --> 01:42:21,685
She left not a clue.

1499
01:42:22,999 --> 01:42:26,126
Clever girl.
And so pretty, so pretty.

1500
01:42:28,696 --> 01:42:32,522
A little old for my taste,
but I can forgive that just this once.

1501
01:42:32,599 --> 01:42:35,668
Nancy, don't scream.

1502
01:42:35,735 --> 01:42:38,036
Whatever he does to you, don't scream.

1503
01:42:38,104 --> 01:42:42,256
She'll scream. I'm gonna take
all night doing dear old Nancy.

1504
01:42:42,323 --> 01:42:45,526
And you're gonna die knowing
that it's all your fault.

1505
01:42:45,622 --> 01:42:48,173
They've all screamed, Hartigan.

1506
01:42:48,279 --> 01:42:50,964
Dozens of them - maybe a hundred.

1507
01:42:51,031 --> 01:42:54,062
Eight years' worth.
Every one of them has screamed.

1508
01:42:54,138 --> 01:42:56,306
And if there weren't
so many people hereabout,

1509
01:42:56,373 --> 01:43:00,199
I would show you how
I'm gonna make dear old Nancy scream.

1510
01:43:00,276 --> 01:43:02,865
It's gonna be one hell of a show!

1511
01:43:11,544 --> 01:43:15,026
<i>This is it.
No way to fight it now.</i>

1512
01:43:15,093 --> 01:43:17,068
<i>No hope left.</i>

1513
01:43:17,174 --> 01:43:18,833
<i>No chance.</i>

1514
01:43:18,929 --> 01:43:22,573
<i>This is it.
This is the end.</i>

1515
01:43:25,201 --> 01:43:26,256
<i>No.</i>

1516
01:43:26,869 --> 01:43:30,964
<i>Give it a shot, old man.
Keep your neck tight. Move.</i>

1517
01:43:31,032 --> 01:43:34,733
<i>The window - maybe there's an alarm.
The window.</i>

1518
01:43:34,801 --> 01:43:37,361
<i>Keep your neck tight, goddamn it!
Stay conscious!</i>

1519
01:43:37,428 --> 01:43:40,113
<i>Stay conscious.</i>

1520
01:43:40,181 --> 01:43:41,322
<i>No alarm.</i>

1521
01:43:41,399 --> 01:43:44,045
<i>The glass! Cut the rope.</i>

1522
01:43:44,113 --> 01:43:46,836
<i>You can do it.
You can do it.</i>

1523
01:43:46,903 --> 01:43:48,524
It is inclement upon me

1524
01:43:48,630 --> 01:43:52,782
to comment with marked displeasure
on your rash impulsiveness

1525
01:43:52,849 --> 01:43:59,342
in selecting such an eye-catching
and impractical car to heist, Mr. Shlubb.

1526
01:43:59,409 --> 01:44:04,846
Irrelevant to said mission is the following
query, which I now put forth to you.

1527
01:44:05,364 --> 01:44:10,831
Wherein this most streamlined
and trunkless of transports -

1528
01:44:10,898 --> 01:44:13,353
boner-inspiring though it may be -

1529
01:44:13,430 --> 01:44:18,129
wherein are we to reposit
our recently deceased cargo?

1530
01:44:21,428 --> 01:44:24,688
I can only express puzzlement
that borders on alarm.

1531
01:44:29,042 --> 01:44:32,552
Tell me where Roark takes the girls
or I'll cut your damn head off!

1532
01:44:32,629 --> 01:44:34,250
In plain English, creep!

1533
01:44:34,327 --> 01:44:37,932
The answer you seek is rural,
even agrarian.

1534
01:44:39,218 --> 01:44:41,222
The farm!

1535
01:44:42,037 --> 01:44:44,885
<i>That's all I need to hear.
Every cop on the force</i>

1536
01:44:44,943 --> 01:44:48,875
<i>knows about the Roark family's farm
and to stay away from it.</i>

1537
01:44:48,980 --> 01:44:51,148
<i>Shlubb and Klump
were packing an arsenal.</i>

1538
01:44:51,215 --> 01:44:54,217
<i>Once things get loud,
I'll probably have use for the cannons.</i>

1539
01:44:54,322 --> 01:44:57,170
<i>But at first, I'll have to play it quiet.</i>

1540
01:44:57,237 --> 01:44:59,376
<i>Quiet and nasty.</i>

1541
01:44:59,923 --> 01:45:03,155
<i>Nancy's car - six miles from the farm.</i>

1542
01:45:03,222 --> 01:45:06,348
<i>"Nobody but me can keep
this heap running", she told me.</i>

1543
01:45:06,415 --> 01:45:09,762
<i>Good girl.
The car stalled out on that yellow bastard</i>

1544
01:45:09,839 --> 01:45:12,112
<i>and you didn't tell him
how to start it up again.</i>

1545
01:45:12,179 --> 01:45:15,948
<i>You kept your mouth shut.
I'll bet Junior was furious.</i>

1546
01:45:16,015 --> 01:45:18,508
<i>I'll bet he slapped you around
something fierce.</i>

1547
01:45:18,576 --> 01:45:22,373
<i>But you stayed strong.
You bought a few extra minutes.</i>

1548
01:45:22,450 --> 01:45:24,589
<i>There's still a chance, Nancy.</i>

1549
01:45:24,694 --> 01:45:26,574
<i>Don't scream.</i>

1550
01:45:27,600 --> 01:45:31,014
<i>I ditch the car a mile or so from the farm
and make my way through the woods.</i>

1551
01:45:31,541 --> 01:45:34,888
<i>I'm not halfway there when it hits.</i>

1552
01:45:35,790 --> 01:45:39,242
<i>My heart.
Can't be my heart.</i>

1553
01:45:39,309 --> 01:45:42,033
<i>I was cured.</i>

1554
01:45:42,100 --> 01:45:44,996
<i>Bad cough - blood in it.</i>

1555
01:45:45,485 --> 01:45:47,049
<i>Doesn't matter now.</i>

1556
01:45:47,125 --> 01:45:50,156
<i>I don't have to stay alive
that much longer, anyway.</i>

1557
01:45:54,644 --> 01:45:57,003
<i>Rotten way to kill a man, but it's quiet.</i>

1558
01:46:02,738 --> 01:46:05,702
<i>Hate yourself later.</i>

1559
01:46:16,845 --> 01:46:19,751
You're only making this worse for yourself,
you stupid cow!

1560
01:46:28,430 --> 01:46:30,770
Do you think I'm tired?

1561
01:46:30,828 --> 01:46:32,870
Is that it?
Do you think I'm getting tired?

1562
01:46:32,976 --> 01:46:35,278
You're the one who's gonna crack!

1563
01:46:35,345 --> 01:46:37,234
You'll crack!

1564
01:46:37,330 --> 01:46:40,226
You'll cry and beg!

1565
01:46:40,303 --> 01:46:41,962
You'll scream!

1566
01:46:42,029 --> 01:46:46,575
Oh, yeah, you'll scream,
you big, fat, ugly cow!

1567
01:46:46,642 --> 01:46:48,071
You'll scream!

1568
01:46:53,451 --> 01:46:55,906
You're thinking the whip
was the worst I could do?

1569
01:46:56,491 --> 01:46:58,888
That was foreplay.

1570
01:46:59,915 --> 01:47:02,734
Hartigan was right about you.

1571
01:47:02,801 --> 01:47:05,170
You can't get it up unless I scream.

1572
01:47:06,762 --> 01:47:08,459
You're pathetic!

1573
01:47:09,706 --> 01:47:11,720
You're pathetic.

1574
01:47:14,003 --> 01:47:16,966
It's not wise at all
to make fun of me like that.

1575
01:47:18,385 --> 01:47:20,744
It brings out the worst in me.

1576
01:47:27,026 --> 01:47:28,714
<i>Stupid old man!</i>

1577
01:47:28,781 --> 01:47:30,852
<i>In too much of a hurry.</i>

1578
01:47:32,425 --> 01:47:35,216
Damn!
It can't be!

1579
01:47:35,695 --> 01:47:39,042
<i>Charging in like Galahad,
just like I told myself I wouldn't!</i>

1580
01:47:39,148 --> 01:47:40,395
<i>Stupid old man!</i>

1581
01:47:40,462 --> 01:47:44,490
- You tagged him good!
- Don't take no chances. Perforate the fool.

1582
01:47:49,035 --> 01:47:50,790
Good advice.

1583
01:48:00,620 --> 01:48:02,759
Give it up, Junior.

1584
01:48:02,826 --> 01:48:04,734
It's over.
Let her go.

1585
01:48:04,850 --> 01:48:06,470
You're dreaming, Hartigan!

1586
01:48:06,576 --> 01:48:11,304
I get to see your eyes while I fillet the
woman of your dreams right in front of you!

1587
01:48:11,371 --> 01:48:14,440
Look at you!
You're about to keel over!

1588
01:48:14,507 --> 01:48:17,163
You can't even lift that cannon!

1589
01:48:17,230 --> 01:48:19,494
Sure, I can.

1590
01:48:26,092 --> 01:48:28,643
You gave me a scare there
for a second there, old man.

1591
01:48:28,719 --> 01:48:31,529
Nancy, I'm sorry.

1592
01:48:32,201 --> 01:48:34,886
I'm taking no chances with you.

1593
01:48:37,322 --> 01:48:40,669
First I soften you up,
and then it's showtime.

1594
01:48:43,786 --> 01:48:46,126
Here it comes.

1595
01:48:47,660 --> 01:48:49,415
It's gonna hurt.

1596
01:48:49,482 --> 01:48:51,429
You're right about that.

1597
01:48:55,111 --> 01:48:56,972
Sucker.

1598
01:49:00,108 --> 01:49:01,834
<i>I take away his weapon.</i>

1599
01:49:03,695 --> 01:49:04,999
<i>Both of them.</i>

1600
01:49:16,363 --> 01:49:19,873
Eight long years, son of a bitch!

1601
01:49:20,871 --> 01:49:24,668
<i>After a while, all I'm doing is pounding
wet chunks of bone into the floorboards,</i>

1602
01:49:24,745 --> 01:49:25,896
<i>so I stop.</i>

1603
01:49:27,373 --> 01:49:29,761
So long, Junior.

1604
01:49:29,837 --> 01:49:32,254
Been a pleasure.

1605
01:49:37,423 --> 01:49:40,770
I didn't scream, Hartigan, not once.

1606
01:49:42,151 --> 01:49:43,647
I didn't scream.

1607
01:49:43,753 --> 01:49:45,795
I know it, baby.

1608
01:49:45,901 --> 01:49:48,135
You grew up strong.

1609
01:49:59,116 --> 01:50:02,338
<i>By the time I get her to the car,
Nancy stops shaking.</i>

1610
01:50:02,406 --> 01:50:06,184
<i>Her skin is warm again.
She's herself again.</i>

1611
01:50:06,251 --> 01:50:08,620
Thanks for remembering my coat.

1612
01:50:09,895 --> 01:50:11,909
And for all the little things.

1613
01:50:12,590 --> 01:50:15,899
Like saving my life, twice.

1614
01:50:16,906 --> 01:50:19,773
- You better get rolling.
- You're not coming along?

1615
01:50:19,879 --> 01:50:24,635
No. I have friends on their way,
to collect evidence.

1616
01:50:24,712 --> 01:50:27,330
I'm gonna blow
this whole sick mess wide open.

1617
01:50:27,397 --> 01:50:29,642
I'm gonna clear my name.

1618
01:50:29,709 --> 01:50:33,602
I'm gonna put Senator Roark
behind bars where he belongs.

1619
01:50:33,669 --> 01:50:37,151
I can't lose you, not again.

1620
01:50:39,433 --> 01:50:42,301
You'll never lose me, Nancy.

1621
01:50:54,509 --> 01:50:58,153
<i>Nancy Callahan, the love of my life.</i>

1622
01:50:59,496 --> 01:51:03,802
<i>Shame to lie to her.
I hope she forgives me for it.</i>

1623
01:51:03,878 --> 01:51:07,331
<i>Get Senator Roark behind bars?
Sure.</i>

1624
01:51:07,398 --> 01:51:10,812
<i>And maybe after I've pulled off
that miracle, I'll go and punch out God.</i>

1625
01:51:10,889 --> 01:51:14,533
<i>There isn't a prosecutor in the state
who'll go after Senator Roark.</i>

1626
01:51:14,600 --> 01:51:16,605
<i>I killed his only son.</i>

1627
01:51:16,710 --> 01:51:18,714
<i>The bloodline is cut.</i>

1628
01:51:18,820 --> 01:51:21,505
<i>Roark's lost his goddamn legacy.</i>

1629
01:51:21,706 --> 01:51:24,286
<i>He'll use all his power
to get revenge on me.</i>

1630
01:51:24,363 --> 01:51:27,806
<i>He'll go after me through Nancy.
He'll find her again.</i>

1631
01:51:28,266 --> 01:51:30,270
<i>There'll be no end to it.</i>

1632
01:51:30,347 --> 01:51:32,447
<i>She'll never be safe.</i>

1633
01:51:32,524 --> 01:51:35,008
<i>Not as long as I'm alive.</i>

1634
01:51:35,075 --> 01:51:37,569
<i>There's only one way to beat him.</i>

1635
01:51:38,182 --> 01:51:40,733
<i>An old man dies,</i>

1636
01:51:40,810 --> 01:51:42,949
<i>a young woman lives.</i>

1637
01:51:44,004 --> 01:51:46,181
<i>Fair trade.</i>

1638
01:51:49,029 --> 01:51:51,848
<i>I love you, Nancy.</i>

1639
01:51:58,533 --> 01:52:00,508
Yes.

1640
01:52:00,585 --> 01:52:02,848
Oh, Mom, don't go on like that.

1641
01:52:02,915 --> 01:52:07,873
It's not the city. I could've gotten
in a traffic accident anywhere.

1642
01:52:07,941 --> 01:52:11,393
Yeah, just a fracture.
The doctor said it's a clean break.

1643
01:52:11,460 --> 01:52:13,733
It should be right as rain in no time.

1644
01:52:17,291 --> 01:52:19,228
Uh-huh.

1645
01:52:27,524 --> 01:52:29,221
Mm-hm.

1646
01:52:32,194 --> 01:52:35,397
<i>Turn the right corner in Sin City</i>

1647
01:52:35,464 --> 01:52:39,770
<i>and you can find anything.</i>

1648
01:52:39,847 --> 01:52:41,468
Becky.

1649
01:52:43,434 --> 01:52:45,985
Care for a smoke?

1650
01:52:47,941 --> 01:52:50,080
Love you, too, Mom.

1651
01:52:52,295 --> 01:52:53,225
<i>Anything.</i>

